nyt = nytimes_county_data()
library(tidycensus)
est_pop = get_estimates('county', product='characteristics',
                        breakdown=c("RACE"), breakdown_labels = TRUE)
#> Fetching characteristics data by state and combining the result.
ds2 = nyt %>%
    dplyr::left_join(est_pop, by=c("fips"="GEOID")) %>%
    dplyr::group_by(date,RACE,subset) %>%
    dplyr::summarize(count=sum(count), value=sum(value)) %>%
    dplyr::mutate(rate = count/value * 100000)
ggplotly(ds2 %>%
         filter(rate>10) %>%
         ggplot(aes(x=date, y=rate, color=RACE)) +
         geom_line() +
         scale_y_log10() +
         theme(legend.position='bottom') +
         facet_grid(rows=vars(subset)))
